From Olanrewaju Lawal,Birnin Kebbi  Please enable JavaScript This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window. Kebbi State Governor, Senator Abubakar Atiku Bagudu, CON has granted an approval for the release of N140 million to civil servants in the state as car, motorcycle and furniture loan. This was contained in a statement signed by the Commissioner for Finance, Ibrahim Muhammad Augie and made available to newsmen in Birnin Kebbi . According to him, “ the loan is to be disbursed to eligible civil servants as car, motorcycle and furniture loan in respective ministries, departments and agencies (MDAs) to be repaid within five years without any interest. “The gesture by the governor is part of his sustained effort to boost the morale of civil servants towards improving their performance. “Civil servants are therefore expected to reciprocate this kind gesture by the governor to be dedicated to their duties”, he added.